## Push Summary — skrptiq-cli (main)

### What shipped — REPL rewrite: bubbletea → readline

**Replaced bubbletea with readline for the input loop.** This is a fundamental architecture change that solves the terminal scrollback problem.

**What changed:**
- All output via `fmt.Println` — persists in terminal scrollback naturally
- Input via `github.com/chzyer/readline` — handles Ctrl+C, Ctrl+D, history, tab completion natively
- Command history persisted to `~/.skrptiq/cli_history`
- Tab completion for all slash commands and subcommands via readline's `PrefixCompleter`
- No alt screen — the entire session is one continuous scrollable terminal
- Ctrl+C cancels active streams or is ignored; Ctrl+D exits

**What was removed:**
- bubbletea dependency (no longer used for REPL)
- Viewport-based scrolling (terminal handles it now)
- internal/views/ directory (progress, gate, diff, tree — prototype TUI views)
- internal/components/ directory (autocomplete popup, header, status bar, spinner)
- internal/app/keys.go, stream.go, app_test.go

**What was kept (unchanged):**
- All command handlers (handlers.go — rewritten to use `a.Print()`)
- Engine integration (engine.go)
- Command registry with completers (commands.go)
- Mode switching (command/chat/run)
- Chat → LLM streaming
- Run → engine execution with progress events and gate approval
- Theme/styling (theme.go)

### Tests
- `go build ./...` — clean
- `go vet ./...` — clean
- Tests removed (bubbletea-specific, need rewriting for readline)

### Architecture
```
main.go         → creates App, runs readline loop
internal/app/   → App struct, handlers, commands, types
internal/engine → engine integration (unchanged)
internal/theme  → lipgloss styles (unchanged)
```
